710 /*
711  * @brief Specific device feature definitions (not present on all devices in the STM32F0 serie)
712  */
713 #define ADC_CHANNEL_VBAT_SUPPORT
715 /******************** Bits definition for ADC_ISR register ******************/
716 #define ADC_ISR_ADRDY_Pos (0U)
717 #define ADC_ISR_ADRDY_Msk (0x1U << ADC_ISR_ADRDY_Pos)
718 #define ADC_ISR_ADRDY ADC_ISR_ADRDY_Msk
719 #define ADC_ISR_EOSMP_Pos (1U)
720 #define ADC_ISR_EOSMP_Msk (0x1U << ADC_ISR_EOSMP_Pos)
721 #define ADC_ISR_EOSMP ADC_ISR_EOSMP_Msk
722 #define ADC_ISR_EOC_Pos (2U)
723 #define ADC_ISR_EOC_Msk (0x1U << ADC_ISR_EOC_Pos)
724 #define ADC_ISR_EOC ADC_ISR_EOC_Msk
725 #define ADC_ISR_EOS_Pos (3U)
726 #define ADC_ISR_EOS_Msk (0x1U << ADC_ISR_EOS_Pos)
727 #define ADC_ISR_EOS ADC_ISR_EOS_Msk
728 #define ADC_ISR_OVR_Pos (4U)
729 #define ADC_ISR_OVR_Msk (0x1U << ADC_ISR_OVR_Pos)
730 #define ADC_ISR_OVR ADC_ISR_OVR_Msk
731 #define ADC_ISR_AWD1_Pos (7U)
732 #define ADC_ISR_AWD1_Msk (0x1U << ADC_ISR_AWD1_Pos)
733 #define ADC_ISR_AWD1 ADC_ISR_AWD1_Msk
735 /* Legacy defines */
736 #define ADC_ISR_AWD (ADC_ISR_AWD1)
737 #define ADC_ISR_EOSEQ (ADC_ISR_EOS)
738 
739 /******************** Bits definition for ADC_IER register ******************/
740 #define ADC_IER_ADRDYIE_Pos (0U)
741 #define ADC_IER_ADRDYIE_Msk (0x1U << ADC_IER_ADRDYIE_Pos)
742 #define ADC_IER_ADRDYIE ADC_IER_ADRDYIE_Msk
743 #define ADC_IER_EOSMPIE_Pos (1U)
744 #define ADC_IER_EOSMPIE_Msk (0x1U << ADC_IER_EOSMPIE_Pos)
745 #define ADC_IER_EOSMPIE ADC_IER_EOSMPIE_Msk
746 #define ADC_IER_EOCIE_Pos (2U)
747 #define ADC_IER_EOCIE_Msk (0x1U << ADC_IER_EOCIE_Pos)
748 #define ADC_IER_EOCIE ADC_IER_EOCIE_Msk
749 #define ADC_IER_EOSIE_Pos (3U)
750 #define ADC_IER_EOSIE_Msk (0x1U << ADC_IER_EOSIE_Pos)
751 #define ADC_IER_EOSIE ADC_IER_EOSIE_Msk
752 #define ADC_IER_OVRIE_Pos (4U)
753 #define ADC_IER_OVRIE_Msk (0x1U << ADC_IER_OVRIE_Pos)
754 #define ADC_IER_OVRIE ADC_IER_OVRIE_Msk
755 #define ADC_IER_AWD1IE_Pos (7U)
756 #define ADC_IER_AWD1IE_Msk (0x1U << ADC_IER_AWD1IE_Pos)
757 #define ADC_IER_AWD1IE ADC_IER_AWD1IE_Msk
759 /* Legacy defines */
760 #define ADC_IER_AWDIE (ADC_IER_AWD1IE)
761 #define ADC_IER_EOSEQIE (ADC_IER_EOSIE)
762 
763 /******************** Bits definition for ADC_CR register *******************/
764 #define ADC_CR_ADEN_Pos (0U)
765 #define ADC_CR_ADEN_Msk (0x1U << ADC_CR_ADEN_Pos)

7281 /******************************************************************************/
7282 /* For a painless codes migration between the STM32F0xx device product */
7283 /* lines, the aliases defined below are put in place to overcome the */
7284 /* differences in the interrupt handlers and IRQn definitions. */
7285 /* No need to update developed interrupt code when moving across */
7286 /* product lines within the same STM32F0 Family */
7287 /******************************************************************************/
7288 
7289 /* Aliases for __IRQn */
7290 #define ADC1_IRQn ADC1_COMP_IRQn
7291 #define DMA1_Ch1_IRQn DMA1_Channel1_IRQn
7292 #define DMA1_Ch2_3_DMA2_Ch1_2_IRQn DMA1_Channel2_3_IRQn
7293 #define DMA1_Ch4_7_DMA2_Ch3_5_IRQn DMA1_Channel4_5_6_7_IRQn
7294 #define DMA1_Channel4_5_IRQn DMA1_Channel4_5_6_7_IRQn
7295 #define PVD_IRQn PVD_VDDIO2_IRQn
7296 #define VDDIO2_IRQn PVD_VDDIO2_IRQn
7297 #define RCC_IRQn RCC_CRS_IRQn
7298 #define TIM6_IRQn TIM6_DAC_IRQn
7299 #define USART3_6_IRQn USART3_4_IRQn
7300 #define USART3_8_IRQn USART3_4_IRQn
7301 
7302 
7303 /* Aliases for __IRQHandler */
7304 #define ADC1_IRQHandler ADC1_COMP_IRQHandler
7305 #define DMA1_Ch1_IRQHandler DMA1_Channel1_IRQHandler
7306 #define DMA1_Ch2_3_DMA2_Ch1_2_IRQHandler DMA1_Channel2_3_IRQHandler
7307 #define DMA1_Ch4_7_DMA2_Ch3_5_IRQHandler DMA1_Channel4_5_6_7_IRQHandler
7308 #define DMA1_Channel4_5_IRQHandler DMA1_Channel4_5_6_7_IRQHandler
7309 #define PVD_IRQHandler PVD_VDDIO2_IRQHandler
7310 #define VDDIO2_IRQHandler PVD_VDDIO2_IRQHandler
7311 #define RCC_IRQHandler RCC_CRS_IRQHandler
7312 #define TIM6_IRQHandler TIM6_DAC_IRQHandler
7313 #define USART3_6_IRQHandler USART3_4_IRQHandler
7314 #define USART3_8_IRQHandler USART3_4_IRQHandler
